A hospital proprietor and two staff members were on Wednesday charged in a Migori court over conspiracy to defraud the National Hospital Insurance Fund (NHIF).
The three – John Nono, proprietor of Gentontira Medical Center in Isebania town, Raymond Kyalo and Quenter Atieno – were arraigned before Resident Magistrate Hellen Maritim for allegedly forging claims amounting to Sh172,000 from patients.



