This came after detectives nabbed them at the hospital on December 31.
According to charges presented in court, the three committed the offense on different dates between October 1 and October 30.
“The three accused persons are hereby charged with conspiracy to defraud NHIF by submitting fake medical claims for 28 patients worth Sh 172,000 in October 2020,” read part of the charge sheet. 
Mr Mwita, was further charged with an attempt to obtain money amounting to Sh172,000 through false pretense.



